```javascript
function groupAnagrams(words) {
  const groups = new Map();

  for (const word of words) {
    const key = [...word].sort().join('');

    if (!groups.has(key)) {
      groups.set(key, []);
    }

    groups.get(key).push(word);
  }

  return [...groups.values()];
}
```

### Example
```javascript
console.log(groupAnagrams(["eat", "tea", "tan", "ate", "nat", "bat"]));
// [["eat", "tea", "ate"], ["tan", "nat"], ["bat"]]
```

### Why this works
- Each word is converted to a canonical anagram key by sorting its letters.
- Words with the same sorted-letter key go into the same group.
- `Map` preserves insertion order, so:
  - words stay in original order within each group
  - groups stay in the order their first word appears

