A **trie** (pronounced “try”), also called a **prefix tree**, is a tree-shaped data structure for storing strings so that common prefixes are shared.

For example, storing:

- `cat`
- `car`
- `dog`

creates a structure like:

```text
root
 ├── c
 │    └── a
 │         ├── t
 │         └── r
 └── d
      └── o
           └── g
```

Each node represents a prefix:
- root = `""`
- path `c -> a` = `"ca"`
- path `d -> o -> g` = `"dog"`

You usually mark nodes where a full word ends.

## Why use a trie

A trie is useful when you need efficient:
- **insert**
- **exact word lookup**
- **prefix lookup**

For lowercase English words, each node can store up to 26 children.

## Time complexity

If `L` is the word length:

- `Insert(word)` → `O(L)`
- `Search(word)` → `O(L)`
- `StartsWith(prefix)` → `O(L)`

This is independent of how many total words are stored.

## Space tradeoff

Tries can use more memory than hash sets because each character may need a node, but they’re very good for prefix-based operations.

---

## C# implementation

This version supports:
- `Insert(string word)`
- `Search(string word)`
- `StartsWith(string prefix)`

```csharp
using System;

public class Trie
{
    private class TrieNode
    {
        public TrieNode[] Children = new TrieNode[26];
        public bool IsEndOfWord;
    }

    private readonly TrieNode _root;

    public Trie()
    {
        _root = new TrieNode();
    }

    public void Insert(string word)
    {
        TrieNode current = _root;

        foreach (char c in word)
        {
            int index = c - 'a';
            if (current.Children[index] == null)
            {
                current.Children[index] = new TrieNode();
            }

            current = current.Children[index];
        }

        current.IsEndOfWord = true;
    }

    public bool Search(string word)
    {
        TrieNode node = Traverse(word);
        return node != null && node.IsEndOfWord;
    }

    public bool StartsWith(string prefix)
    {
        return Traverse(prefix) != null;
    }

    private TrieNode Traverse(string s)
    {
        TrieNode current = _root;

        foreach (char c in s)
        {
            int index = c - 'a';
            if (current.Children[index] == null)
            {
                return null;
            }

            current = current.Children[index];
        }

        return current;
    }
}
```

---

## Example usage

```csharp
public class Program
{
    public static void Main()
    {
        Trie trie = new Trie();

        trie.Insert("apple");

        Console.WriteLine(trie.Search("apple"));     // True
        Console.WriteLine(trie.Search("app"));       // False
        Console.WriteLine(trie.StartsWith("app"));   // True

        trie.Insert("app");
        Console.WriteLine(trie.Search("app"));       // True
    }
}
```

---

